      ],
      "orig": "Andrew Duncan was bom in London,U.K.,in 1960. He received a B.S.degree in engineering and-applied sciences from the California Institute of Technology in1983.Hetaught high school physics for 2years in Pasadena, California,while studying at Caltech,and for anotheryear after graduation.He then worked for 2years,with Marshall Buck,as a programmer at Cerwin-Vega Inc.Mr.Duncan is currentlya doctoral student inmathematicsat the Universityof California at Santa Cruz,where he is studying the application of group theory to the thcory of tonal harmony. He has also worked as a consultant at E-mu Systems,Inc.in the area of digital pitch shifting.",
      "text": "Andrew Duncan was bom in London,U.K.,in 1960. He received a B.S.degree in engineering and-applied sciences from the California Institute of Technology in1983.Hetaught high school physics for 2years in Pasadena, California,while studying at Caltech,and for anotheryear after graduation.He then worked for 2years,with Marshall Buck,as a programmer at Cerwin-Vega Inc.Mr.Duncan is currentlya doctoral student inmathematicsat the Universityof California at Santa Cruz,where he is studying the application of group theory to the thcory of tonal harmony. He has also worked as a consultant at E-mu Systems,Inc.in the area of digital pitch shifting."
    },
